The paper focuses on improving the fluency of natural language generation tasks using a novel addition to the seq2seq neural network architecture. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.NE. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on tasks such as machine translation and text summarization, which are often studied in the sub-category of cs.CV (computer vision) due to their reliance on image captioning.
